  "commentary": "With SPX at 7087.49 sitting just above the GEX flip at 7083, dealers are in PIN regime and long gamma, meaning they'll mechanically sell any rally and buy dips to hedge their books. The massive positive gamma wall at 7200 (+7.2B) creates a strong ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the negative gamma floor at 7040 provides downside support through dealer buying. Current spot is caught between supportive gamma at 7100 (+4.6B) below and resistance building toward 7150 (+4.9B), suggesting range-bound action with mean reversion tendencies.\n\nBottom line: expect sideways chop between 7040-7150 with dealers capping moves.",
